The city will host the inaugural Kerala Literature Festival from February 4.About 150 leading writers in the country will take part in the four-day international festival. The venue will be the beach, which will have four makeshift stages.A 101-member reception committee with Kozhikode Mayor V.K.C. Mammed Koya as chairman and A.K. Abdul Hakkim as general convener has been constituted. Noted poet K. Satchidanandan, who is also the festival director, and D.C. Kizhakemuri Foundationâ€™s (DCKF) Ravi D.C. are the chief coordinators.Writers Taslima Nasreen, M.T. Vasudevan Nair, M. Mukundan, Gita Hariharan, Subroto Bagchi, Prathiba Ray, Ashok Vajpeyi, Anand, K.R. Meera, Santhosh Echikkanam, E. Santhosh Kumar, Anitha Nair, T.D. Ramakrishnan, K.P. Ramanunni, Sarah Joseph, Paul Zachariah, Benyamin, Leena Manimala, Meena Kandaswamy, T.M. Krishna will take part in the festival.Mammootty, Manju Warrier, Mattanur Sankarankutty, Rajashree Warrier will be part of the cultural events of the festival.Minister for Social Justice and Panchayats M.K. Muneer released the logo designed by Riyaz Komu. The Mayor also launched a websitewww.keralaliterature festival.comon the occasion.The organisers said that the State with the highest literacy rate has been home to many writers who have been acclaimed in both national and international arena.